description._content: Catalog #: 09_01651 Title: First Lieutenant Harry Haw Special Collection Photo Long Beach California Additional Information: Air Corps Detachment of the U.S. Army. Long Beach California 1934. Left to right. Front row: ?, John Van Horn, Jack A. Moore, R. Hutton. Second row: Dr. Sauer, W.D. Lucy, Nissley, Lees, Douglas Kelly, Harry Haw, Dr. Browne. Back row standing: Remelin, Bill Von Dusen, Nunn, Jim Liddell, Gore, Frank Page, Sefton Wakefield, Harry Haw served in the U.S. Army in the 514th Observation Squadron. He entered the U.S. Army in 1917 and became a First Lieutenant in 1930. He became a civilian Transport Pilot by 1930 and had logged 789 flying hours by 1934. he later became Principal of the Alice Birney school.
